---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'About — Meridian',
  description: 'Why Meridian was built, and who built it.',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest text-emerald-700 uppercase mb-4">Our mission</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-6 leading-snug">
        Give every trader a clear view of themselves — in real time.
      </h1>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed text-base">
        <p>
          The trading industry is full of tools that help you analyze the market. Almost none of them help you analyze yourself.
        </p>
        <p>
          Meridian was built to fill that gap. Not with a journal you fill in after the session. Not with a generic mood tracker. But with a real-time behavioral index that runs natively inside NinjaTrader 8 and shows you, in numbers, how behavioral pressure is building from your session activity — before the next trade.
        </p>
        <p>
          We believe that most traders already have what it takes. A solid strategy. A plan. Discipline — most of the time. What they lack is a mirror. Something that shows them when the plan is quietly slipping, before it becomes a blown session.
        </p>
        <p>
          That is what Meridian is.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Divider -->
  <div class="border-t border-zinc-100"></div>

  <!-- Founder story -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest text-emerald-700 uppercase mb-4">Why Meridian exists</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-6 leading-snug">
        I spent years looking for a better strategy.<br />I had it the whole time.
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed text-base">
        <p>
          I've been a full-time trader for over five years — starting in equities, moving to prop firm futures, and now trading independently. In that time, I've blown up more accounts than I care to admit.
        </p>
        <p>
          It was never the strategy. I knew exactly what to do. The problem was that in the middle of a losing streak — three red trades in a row, already past my session limit, telling myself <em>"just one more"</em> — I couldn't see what was happening to me. I was tilted. My emotions had taken over. And no strategy survives that.
        </p>
        <p>
          After years of that same pattern — the self-doubt, the frustration, the questions about why I couldn't just <em>stick to the plan</em> — I started building what I wished had existed: a tool that tells you, in real time, where you stand psychologically. Not a journal you fill in after the damage is done. Something that works <em>during</em> the session.
        </p>
        <p class="font-semibold text-zinc-900">
          Since building Meridian, I've passed multiple prop firm evaluations, collected consistent payouts, and now trade independently full-time. Not because I found a better strategy. Because I finally stopped being my own worst enemy.
        </p>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-zinc-400 font-medium">— Gary Caffrey, Founder of Meridian</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Divider -->
  <div class="border-t border-zinc-100"></div>

  <!-- What we're building -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 bg-zinc-50/60">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest text-emerald-700 uppercase mb-4">What we're building</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-6 leading-snug">
        Starting with NinjaTrader 8. More platforms coming.
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed text-base">
        <p>
          Meridian is currently built for NinjaTrader 8, the platform where most serious retail futures traders operate. It runs as a native add-on — fully local, no cloud, no accounts, no data leaving your machine.
        </p>
        <p>
          Future versions will expand to additional platforms and trading environments. The goal is the same regardless of platform: give traders a precise, real-time view of behavioral stability signals from their session, so they can make a calmer decision about whether to keep trading.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PSI scope — behavioral proxy -->
  <section class="py-12 px-6 bg-zinc-50/80 border-t border-zinc-100">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">
        PSI is a behavioral proxy index derived from your trading activity inside NinjaTrader. It does not measure physiology (for example heart rate or stress hormones), and it is not validated as a predictor of trading profits or losses. Meridian is designed to improve self-awareness and discipline during a session; outcomes still depend on many factors beyond psychology.
        <span class="block mt-2 italic text-zinc-400">Results may vary. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-white border-t border-zinc-100 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-3">Try it free for 7 days.</h2>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 text-base mb-8">No charge during the trial. Cancel any time.</p>
      <a
        href="/pricing"
        class="inline-block bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 text-white font-semibold px-8 py-3 rounded-full transition-colors"
      >
        Start free trial — 7 days
      </a>
      <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-zinc-400">$49.99/month after trial · NinjaTrader 8 required · Trading involves substantial risk of loss</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
